com.yantra.yfc.rcp

Class YRCWizardRule2

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yantra.yfc.rcp.YRCWizardRule2

  • public abstract class YRCWizardRule2
extends java.lang.Object
    Abstract class which needs to be implemented by classes which need to act as Rules based on which wizard flow is determined.
    NOTE: Only one object is created and used throughout the wizard lifecycle.
    See Also:
    YRCWizard, IYRCWizardRule

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        public abstract java.lang.String execute()
        This method will be called when the wizard flow needs the output value of this rule. Wizard flow is based on the output of this rule, as defined in the wizard definition xml.
        NOTE:
        • This method will be called in the background thread. Do not access any UI components during this method call.
        Returns:
        The output value of the rule.

      • handleRuleCompletion

        public final void handleRuleCompletion()
        This method is called when the rule completes, post rule processing methods are called from this method.
        API calls should not be made in this method.

      • handleCompletion

        public abstract void handleCompletion()
        This method is called when the rule completes, post rule processing should be done here.
        This method will be called in the ui thread.
